priceShippingInformation: FREE delivery Tuesday, November 4 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35 Or Prime members get FREE delivery Saturday, November 1. Order within 7 hrs 29 mins. Join Prime
productDescription: Do you like to travel and solve puzzles? Then this book is for you. In this book you will find 12 puzzles of logic and adventure, divided into 6 mazes and 6 sudokus, that will make you enjoy the road and exercise your mind. Each puzzle has a theme related to travel, such as destinations, means of transport, monuments, cultures, etc. In addition, each puzzle has a solution and an explanation that will teach you something new and curious about the world. This book is ideal to take with you on the plane, train, bus or car, and to share it with your friends, family or travel companions. Don’t get bored on the road, have fun and learn with these puzzles of logic and adventure. Instructions: To solve the puzzles in this book, you only need a pencil or a pen and a lot of desire to have fun and learn. The puzzles are divided into two types: mazes and sudokus. Here we explain how to solve each one of them: Mazes: A maze is a labyrinth that has an entrance and an exit. The objective is to find the path that connects the entrance with the exit, without passing through the walls or the obstacles that are in the labyrinth. To solve a maze, you can use the method you prefer, such as following the right hand, the left hand, the wall method or the rope method. You can also use your intuition and your sense of direction. When you find the path, mark it with your pencil or pen and check the solution at the end of the book. Sudokus: A sudoku is a puzzle that consists of a 9x9 cell grid, divided into 9 regions of 3x3 cells. The objective is to fill in the empty cells with the numbers from 1 to 9, so that each row, each column and each region contains the nine numbers without repeating. To solve a sudoku, you can use logic, deduction, elimination and other techniques that help you place the numbers correctly. When you fill in all the cells, check the solution at the end of the book." Read more
